I went into this location around 8pm December 2016. There were 2 employees and they started laughing suspiciously when I walked in, the kind of laugh that school kids make when they pull a prank and they're laughing at you because you're about to be the brunt of a joke. The store  Anyway, I was really hungry so I reluctantly ordered a sandwich but I didn't have that confidence that I usually have at Jimmy Johns that the place is sanitary so I took a couple bites of my sandwich but I couldn't enjoy it.  It wasn't just paranoia though because the location really did not look well kept and clean.

I have eaten at this location many times. The cons are that the sandwiches taste mediocre at best. They are practically flavorless. The pros are that the location is convenient, orders are made quickly, and the prices are relatively cheap. What one should expect from Jimmy John's is a sub-optimal sandwich, delivered quickly, and priced reasonably considering the quality. After eating here, I often have a sensation of regret that I didn't spend a little more money to get a better sandwich elsewhere.

The lady taking my order was very nice and tried to help as much as she could. The lady making the sandwich was very rude and disrespectful. I ordered 16 sandwiches, and asked for the oil and vinegar on the side and she would not allow it. I even offered to pay for a cup so they could put it in there for me and with no remorse she responses no we aren't doing that. Her attitude was very unprofessional and uncalled for. I wanted to walk out, but my coworkers for the NBA really wanted the sandwich. I had to go to rouses by the dome to get vinaigrette and not have their homemade one because she refused to be nice and helpful.

This is frustrating because your sandwiches are already high, then you add a delivery fee, and a tip, but I can't get napkins. Please fix this.

Ordered online. They delivered the wrong order (the delivery man just left the sandwiches in the lobby unattended). When we called the restaurant, they refused to acknowledge their mistake (we had the receipt and the email confirmation that showed that order was placed correctly) . After a lot of arguing they sent us the correct sandwich and asked for their old order back. The delivery man was VERY rude when he came back to deliver the correct order. I have long been a JJ fan, but will not be ordering from them...at least not from this location....again.

Changed my 4* rating to a 1. I entered the restaurant and was greeted by a man who yelled at me. He said that their restroom was only for paying customers. I hadn't gone to the restroom yet, and was trying to navigate around the wet floor signs. I frequent the restaurant during my breaks. I'm an uber and lyft driver. It's the only place to get a quick dinner. After I went to the counter I asked a different man what the rude man's name and he refused to give it to me, and so did the other employees. They were all rude. Never again.

Food was good.  I went through a terrible ordering experience all to be told a total and then for someone else to pop on the phone to tell me they do not deliver to my office.  1/2 block away.  I called back and offered to walk the half block to meet the delivery guy.  They agreed.  I waited 25 min in the rain.  I could have walked to JJ and back with my order.  It took me calling to get an update on my order to get the food.  Stay away from lunch time in the NOLA CBD.

Ordered online for delivery to our hotel, literally across the street. They messed up the order, so I called the store. The phone rang and rang, with nobody answering, so we never got it fixed. Eventually (after showing and getting dressed) went by in person to discuss our earlier issue, and was told the manager would give me a call. I never heard from him, despite calling again to remind him/them of the issue.  Our first experience with the product itself was disappointing. The customer service, however, is disgustingly nonexistent.
